[appendix]
[[A-microgpt]]
== Appendix A: microGPT in Scheme — Complete Runnable Code

This appendix assembles every Scheme snippet from the book into a single file, `src/lisp/microgpt.scm`, with all dependencies resolved.
You can run it with any R7RS-compatible Scheme implementation (Chicken Scheme recommended).

=== Installation & Running

[source,bash]
----
# Install Chicken Scheme (Ubuntu/Debian)
apt-get install chicken-bin

# Run the full demo
csi -s src/lisp/microgpt.scm

# Or with Guile
guile src/lisp/microgpt.scm
----

=== Annotated Assembly

The complete `microgpt.scm` is in `src/lisp/microgpt.scm`.
It is organized in dependency order:

1. *Matrix primitives* — `make-matrix`, `mat-mul`, `mat-add`, `mat-scale`, `mat-transpose`, `hstack`
2. *Activations* — `softmax`, `softmax-rows`, `gelu`, `sigmoid`
3. *Embeddings* — `make-embedding-matrix`, `embed-sequence`
4. *Positional encoding* — `make-pe-matrix`, `add-positional-encoding`
5. *Attention* — `scaled-dot-product-attention`, `causal-mask`
6. *Multi-head attention* — `multi-head-attention`
7. *FFN* — `ffn-forward`
8. *Layer norm* — `layer-norm-matrix`
9. *Transformer block* — `transformer-block-forward`
10. *GPT model* — `gpt-forward`, `generate`

=== microGPT Architecture Summary (Reference)

[cols="3,2,2,3",options="header"]
|===
|Component |Input |Output |Parameters

|Token Embedding |`[T]` ints |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[|V| \times d]
|Positional Embedding |`[T]` positions |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[T_{max} \times d]
|× N Transformer Blocks | | |
|— LayerNorm 1 |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |`2d`
|— Multi-Head Attn |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[4d^2]
|— Residual |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |0
|— LayerNorm 2 |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |`2d`
|— FFN |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[8d^2]
|— Residual |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |0
|Final LayerNorm |stem:[[T \times d\]] |stem:[[T \times d\]] |`2d`
|Unembedding |`[d]` |stem:[[|V|\]] |stem:[d \times |V|] (tied)
|===

*Total parameters:* stem:[2|V|d + T_{max}\cdot d + N(12d^2 + 4d) + 2d]

For GPT-2 small: `d=768, N=12, |V|=50257, T_max=1024` → ~117M params.
